-- China Comm. Construction Interested in Chile Bridge, DF Says
-- B y   R a n d a l l   W o o d s
-- 2012-08-16T18:32:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-16/china-comm-construction-interested-in-chile-bridge-df-says.html
China Communications Construction
Company Ltd. (1800)  may send engineers to study the feasibility of
building a bridge linking Chile’s Chiloe Island to the South
American nation’s mainland, Santiago-based newspaper Diario
Financiero  reported today , citing the head of Chile’s foreign
investment committee Matias Mori.  The Chinese company may compete in bidding to develop the
bridge, which would run 2.6 kilometers (1.6 miles) over the
Chacao Channel in southern Chile, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Woods in Santiago at 
 rwoods13@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Philip Sanders at 
 psanders@bloomberg.net  